
    Madhya Pradesh: India election results show nail-biting contest

        

    
        
                
                Image copyright
                 Getty Images
                
            
            
            Image caption
                
                    India will hold general elections in 2019
                
            Early state election results in the central state of Madhya Pradesh show a nail-biting contest between India's ruling BJP and opposition Congress.The leads show a late comeback for the BJP in the central state. Early results showed a clear lead for the Congress.However, Congress is leading in Rajasthan and Chhattisgarh, which were previous BJP strongholds.Correspondents say the losses are a predictable and likely temporary backlash against incumbent parties.India will hold nation-wide parliamentary elections early in 2019. 
    
        

    
      
              
