        Election results are also being declared for the southern state of Telangana and the northeastern state of Mizoram.  Regional parties - the Telangana Rashtra Samiti (TRS) and the Mizo National Front (MNF) - are leading in these states.Indian rupee hit by shock resignation, polls
Why India's Narendra Modi remains star BJP vote-catcher
Is Narendra Modi losing his mojo?
Can Rahul Gandhi revive India's Grand Old Party?
The Congress was widely expected to win in the northern state of Rajasthan, while the central state of Madhya Pradesh was always seen as a close contest between the two parties. But early results in the central state of Chhattisgarh, where the Congress is ahead by a wide margin, have been the most surprising. BBC Hindi's Nitin Srivastava who is in Rajasthan, has been posting photos of the starkly different atmospheres at the BJP and Congress party offices in the state.  
    
        
